The '''Eltro Information Rate Changer''' is an [[analog recording]] tool used to modulate [[Pitch (music)|pitch]] without affecting [[tempo]]. It is best known as the effect used in ''[[2001: A Space Odyssey]]'' for the [[Hal 9000]] computer.<ref name="Langford2013">{{cite book|last=Langford|first=Simon|title=Digital Audio Editing: Correcting and Enhancing Audio in Pro Tools, Logic Pro, Cubase, and Studio One|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=9achAQAAQBAJ&pg=PA239|year=2013|publisher=CRC Press|isbn=978-1-134-11130-5|page=239}}</ref><ref name="Krapp2011">{{cite book|last=Krapp|first=Peter|title=Noise Channels: Glitch and Error in Digital Culture|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=w4k0WhZNNp4C&pg=PA65|year=2011|publisher=University of Minnesota Press|isbn=978-0-8166-7624-8|page=65}}</ref> Patents for the device date back to the 1920s.<ref name="Langford2013"/>

